<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 3 Arrested Over Star Wars Theft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MENOMONIE, Wis. (AP) -- Three men were arrested Wednesday for  
stealing a copy of ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace'' 
from a theater last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	The three men, one 25 and two 22, turned themselves in on  
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The reel of film, which weighed more than 40 pounds, was taken  
off the projection system in the State Theater in Menomonie between 
the Friday and Saturday showings, theater owner Nick LeGros said. 
</P>
<P>
	The film's value on the black market has been estimated to be  
more than $60,000. The theater has received a backup copy but 
LeGros said he lost about $4,000 by not having the movie Saturday 
</P>
<P>
	The film was not believed to have been copied.  
</P>
<P>
	``Our investigation revealed that they weren't in it for a  
profit motive,'' Police Chief Dennis Beety said. 
</P>
<P>
	A 5-foot length of the film was found crumpled and dirty in a  
field near the theater on Tuesday. The remainder of the film was 
recovered in three garbage bags, police said Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
