<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> French Open Tennis Glance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- A look at Wednesday's play in the French Open:  
</P>
<P>
	Attendance: 33,292 at Roland Garros stadium (33,621 in 1998).  
</P>
<P>
	Weather: Sunny with afternoon highs of 72 F.  
</P>
<P>
	Men's winners: Carlos Moya (4), Tim Henman (7), Marcelo Rios  
(9), Greg Rusedski (12) and Andre Agassi (13). 
</P>
<P>
	Women's winners: Martina Hingis (1), Jana Novotna (4), Venus  
Williams (5), Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario (7) and Barbara Schett (15). 
</P>
<P>
	Losers: Yevgeny Kafelnikov (1) lost to Dominik Hrbaty and  
Richard Krajicek (5) bowed to Vincent Spadea. 
</P>
<P>
	On the women's side, Sandrine Testud (12) lost to Mariaan De  
Swardt. 
</P>
<P>
	Thursday's schedule: Pete Sampras (2) plays Andrei Medvedev.  
Patrick Rafter (3) meets Nicolas Escude. Alex Corretja (6) faces 
Fernando Vincente. Gustavo Kuerten (8) plays Guillermo Canas. Felix 
Mantilla (14) is up against Mariano Puerta and Thomas Enqvist (16) 
faces Christian Ruud. 
</P>
<P>
	On the women's side, Lindsay Davenport (2) meets Justine Henin.  
Monica Seles (3) plays Lubomira Bacheva. Steffi Graf (6) faces Ines 
Gorrochategui. Mary Pierce (8) is up against Conchita Martinez. 
Nathalie Tauziat (9) meets Gala Leon Garcia. Patty Schnyder (11) 
plays Nicole Arendt and Julie Halard Decugis (16) faces Elena 
Wagner. 
</P>
<P>
	Quote: ``It's like a big rucksack of stones has fallen off my  
back,'' Martina Hingis after winning her match against French 
favorite Amelie Mauresmo. 
</P>
<P>
	Stat of the day: One ton -- the amount of bananas eaten by  
players during the French Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
