<HEADLINE> Devil Rays' Pitcher on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Devil Rays placed  
pitcher Rolando Arrojo on the 15-day disabled list today with right 
shoulder inflammation. 
</P>
<P>
	Arrojo has struggled, going 2-5 with an 7.31 ERA in nine starts.  
The 1998 American League rookie of the year runnerup reported 
weakness in his shoulder after his last start Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``He had an MRI (Wednesday), which actually turned out to be  
very good. I think it looks more on the positive side that he'll 
come back in two weeks and pitch, ``Tampa Bay manager Larry 
Rothschild said prior to Wednesday night's game against Texas. 
``There is some inflammation, probably not that much out of the 
ordinary for a pitcher in the major leagues. We need to get it 
quieted down.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Arrojo became the team's 13th player on the DL this year.  
</P>
<P>
	He will likely make at least one minor league rehab start before  
rejoining the team. He is eligible to come off the disabled list on 
June 9. 
</P>
<P>
	Bryan Rekar will take Arrojo's spot in the rotation. The  
right-hander has made 11 appearances, including three starts, in 
posting a 3-1 record with a 4.76 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	The Devil Rays recalled pitcher Mike Duvall from Triple-A Durham  
to fill Arrojo's roster spot. The left-hander appeared in nine 
games (0-0, 3.18 ERA) with Tampa Bay before being optioned to 
Durham on April 23. 
</P>
