<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Reagan License Plates Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Ronald Reagan, cowboy hat, riding into the  
Western sunset. It could happen again. 
</P>
<P>
	The state Assembly approved a measure Tuesday on a vote of 62-7  
that calls for commemorative license plates stamped with the 
likeness of the former president, actor and California governor. 
</P>
<P>
	``I can't think of anyone who was more important to  
California,'' said Assemblyman Tony Strickland, a Republican. The 
Ronald Reagan Presidential Library is in his district. 
</P>
<P>
	The design of the plate hasn't been worked out, but Strickland  
said he hoped it would feature Reagan in a cowboy hat, reminiscent 
of the Western movies that made him so popular. 
</P>
<P>
	The measure now goes to the state Senate.  
</P>
<P>
	The Reagan plate would be California's first to honor an  
individual, said Bill Gengler of the Department of Motor Vehicles. 
The state already has 52 specialized and commemorative plates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
