<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NC Student Charged After Bombs Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FAIRMONT, N.C. (AP) -- A high school senior who allegedly  
threatened to blow up his school when he learned he was not going 
to graduate was arrested after two bombs were found in his home. 
</P>
<P>
	Kenneth Harold Bell, 18, a senior at Fairmont High School, was  
arrested Friday and remained in jail Wednesday on $25,000 bond, 
said Lt. Kenneth Sealey of the Robeson County Sheriff's Department. 
He is charged with possession of a weapon of mass destruction. 
</P>
<P>
	When Bell learned several weeks ago he was not going to graduate  
with his class because of excessive absences he told another 
student, ``If I do not graduate, then I will blow up the school,'' 
according to police reports. 
</P>
<P>
	A student at the school found two notes signed by Bell on May 20  
that suggested he was going to kill himself. Police searched his 
home and learned he had assembled two bombs. 
</P>
<P>
	Bell's stepfather found the bombs and disposed of them, police  
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
