<DOCNO> APW19990526.0050 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 10:11:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Damages Oklahoma St. Arena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STILLWATER, Okla. (AP) -- Fire damaged the Gallagher-Iba Arena on  
the Oklahoma State University campus today. 
</P>
<P>
	The blaze began around 9:30 a.m. in a first floor electrical and  
mechanical room and spread to the second floor, where offices are 
located, Stillwater Fire Chief Larry Mullikin said. No one was 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
	The blaze did not reach the arena floor and did not affect the  
building's structural integrity, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had quite a bit of heavy smoke inside, but we were able to  
confine the fire,'' Mullikin said. 
</P>
<P>
	The damage occurred in the southwest corner of the arena, which  
is undergoing a $40 million expansion. Mullikin said the sprinkler 
system had been disconnected during the construction without 
notification to fire officials. 
</P>
<P>
	``When we charged the sprinkler system, it just flooded the  
basement,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mullikin did not have damage estimates and said the state fire  
marshal's office is investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
