<DOCNO> APW19990526.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 06:51:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Exchange Moves To Stop Sell-Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) -- Thai government and stock exchange  
officials said Wednesday that they were working on measures to 
prevent the dumping of stocks after a sell-off prompted complaints 
of manipulation from dealers and investors. 
</P>
<P>
	A large programmed order launched just two minutes before the  
close on Tuesday forced the main Stock Exchange of Thailand index 
down 4 percent. The market closed at 451.05, a fall of 18.93 
points. 
</P>
<P>
	Critics claimed the dumping was aimed at manipulating the index  
so that profits could be taken on index options overseas. 
</P>
<P>
	Thai Deputy Finance Minister Pisit Leeahtam said Wednesday he  
had been briefed on the sell-off by the Securities and Exchange 
Commission and that the government was looking into ways to deal 
with the problem. 
</P>
<P>
	The sell-off caused three blue-chip Thai stocks -- Siam Cement,  
Siam City Cement and Siam Makro -- to fall by more than 30 percent, 
and several dealers said the drop was not warranted. 
</P>
<P>
	``Somebody is trying to manipulate the market,'' Marc Lavoie, an  
analyst at Asset Plus Securities, was quoted as saying by The 
Nation newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
	``Fundamentally, there is nothing wrong, and there have been no  
changes over these stocks. Someone will be in trouble,'' he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990526.0056 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 14:11:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Vince Carter Named Top NBA Rookie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Vince Carter of the Toronto Raptors was the  
overwhelming choice today as the NBA's rookie of the year, 
capturing the award with 113 of 118 votes in a panel of media 
voting. 
</P>
<P>
	Sacramento's Jason Williams received three votes and Boston's  
Paul Pierce got two. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter was the fifth selection in the 1998 NBA draft and  
averaged 18.3 points, 5.7 rebounds and 3.0 assists for the Raptors. 
He was the team's leading scorer, hitting 20 or more points 20 
times and 30 or more three times. 
</P>
<P>
	An early entry player out of the University of North Carolina,  
Carter was drafted by Golden State and then swapped almost 
immediately to Toronto in exchange for cash and his college 
teammate, Antawn Jamison, who was the No. 4 pick. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter is the second Raptor to win the award. Damon Stoudamire,  
who was traded to the Portland Trail Blazers in 1998, was rookie of 
the year in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	The award is sponsored by Schick.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
