<HEADLINE> Interest Rates Up in T-Bill Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The interest rate on 52-week Treasury bills  
rose in Tuesday's auction to the highest level in more than two 
months. 
</P>
<P>
	The discount rate was 4.630 percent, up from 4.490 percent at  
the last auction on April 27. It was the highest rate since 52-week 
bills sold for 4.665 percent on March 2. 
</P>
<P>
	The bills will carry an equivalent coupon interest rate of 4.879  
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,531.90. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales totaled $10 billion out of bids of $22.7 billion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
