<HEADLINE> Mariners Claim Rodriguez from Twins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Seattle Mariners have claimed right-handed  
pitcher Frankie Rodriguez off waivers from Minnesota. He'll join 
the team Friday in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez, 26, was 3-4, with a 6.70 ERA in nine starts this  
season for the Twins' AAA farm club at Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
	On May 8, he threw a complete game no-hitter at Iowa.  
</P>
<P>
	To make room on the roster, the Mariners have designated pitcher  
Greg McCarthy for assignment. He appeared in 18 games in relief 
this year for the Tacoma farm club. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mariners have 10 days to trade McCarthy or release him  
outright. 
</P>
