<HEADLINE> Mom Sentenced in Drug Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GLENWOOD SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) -- A mother who prosecutors said  
used her 7-year-old daughter as a Spanish translator in a cocaine 
deal has been sentenced to five years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Blanca Isiordia Flores, 26, and her husband, Alfredo  
Verra-Figuroa, 22, were sentenced Tuesday in District Court after 
pleading guilty to cocaine distribution charges. Verra-Figuroa also 
was sentenced to five years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Police charged that when undercover agents arrived to buy drugs,  
the little girl said, `Mommy's downstairs weighing it.''' 
</P>
<P>
	The girl was placed in her grandparents' custody.  
