<HEADLINE> 5 1/4 Pct. Rate on Two-Year T-Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on two-year Treasury notes rose in  
Wednesday's auction to the highest level in almost a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield was 5.315 percent, up from 5.017 percent at the last  
auction on April 28. It was the highest rate since two-year notes 
sold for 5.475 percent on July 29, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 5.25 percent with  
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,987.80. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $15 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling  
$30.3 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
