<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Employee Behind O'Hairs' Deaths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Authorities said for the first time Wednesday  
that missing atheist leader Madalyn Murray O'Hair and two of her 
adult children were dead, accusing a former employee of 
orchestrating their murders. 
</P>
<P>
	The accusations against David Waters and three others came in a  
36-page affidavit filed in court by the Internal Revenue Service. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. O'Hair, whose 1963 Supreme Court case led to the ban on  
organized prayer in public schools, vanished from San Antonio with 
her son, Jon Garth Murray, and granddaughter Robin Murray, and 
$500,000 in gold coins. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Waters, who is jailed in Austin on weapons  
charges, allegedly orchestrated the plot to steal at least $600,000 
from Ms. O'Hair's United Secularists of America. 
</P>
<P>
	But he also hated Ms. O'Hair, authorities said, fantasizing  
about ``seeing Madalyn suffer, and snipping off her toes.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The document names Waters; Gary Karr, imprisoned in Detroit;  
Danny Fry, who was killed shortly after the O'Hairs vanished; and 
Gerald Lee Osborne. 
</P>
<P>
	The affidavit, used to obtain a search warrant of Waters'  
apartment, was unsealed on the eve of his scheduled court 
appearance on the weapons charge. 
</P>
<P>
	Waters' lawyer, Patrick Ganne, told the San Antonio Express-News  
that he hadn't seen the document. 
</P>
<P>
	Waters has not been charged with the O'Hair murders.  
</P>
<P>
	The affidavit, however, said Waters was responsible for the  
death of Fry, whose headless, handless body was dumped in Dallas 
County on Oct. 2, 1995, two days after the O'Hairs vanished. 
</P>
<P>
	Waters, who worked for Ms. O'Hair in 1993 and 1994, ``was open  
about his dislike of the O'Hairs and made comments about harming 
Madalyn,'' the document said, citing an informant. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities have theorized the O'Hairs' remains were buried in  
barrels, but two searches of a ranch near San Antonio recently 
failed to find either barrels or bodies. 
</P>
<P>
	According to a second confidential informant, Karr has talked  
about Waters committing four murders in Texas, following a card 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	``After the card game, Waters drove four people involved in the  
card game back home. Waters killed them, took the jewelry, (rings 
and Rolexes) off the bodies, and buried them in a field in Texas 
near a subdivision,'' the affidavit said. 
</P>
<P>
	Waters used a van rented by Karr to transport the bodies, and  
Karr told the informant that one of the persons killed was a woman 
named O'Hair, her daughter and son and another man, the affidavit 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
