<P>
	Analysts expect the company to report a loss of 9 cents per  
share in the second quarter. The company's CEO said that as usual, 
Music Land will count on a big fourth quarter to push it into 
profitability for the year. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Visx, down 6 1/8 at 49 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reported in Wednesday's edition that  
Visx faces federal actions and litigation over patents for its 
laser eye surgery. A number of competing companies are also 
beginning to perform the surgery, intended to correct 
nearsightedness. 

</P>
<P>
 *7th Level Inc., up 1 at 6 15/32    	
</P>
<P>
	IBM plans to use the company's Streammaker technology, made by  
the 7th Street.com division. Streammaker allows Web users to hear 
audio and see video without downloading massive files. 

</P>
<P>
 *Platinum Technology International Inc., up 2 15/16 at 28 15/16  
</P>
<P>
 *Computer Associates International Inc., up 1/4 at 45 on the NYSE 
</P>
<P>
	Computer Associates won Justice Department approval Tuesday for  
its proposed $3.5 billion acquisition of Platinum Tech after 
agreeing to sell off a number of software assets. 

</P>
<P>
 *Take Two Interactive, up 9/16 at 8 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company earned 8 cents a share in the second quarter,  
beating analysts' estimates of 4 cents a share. In last year's 
second quarter, Take Two earned 3 cents per share. Take Two makes 
computer games. 

</P>
</TEXT>
