<DOCNO> APW19990526.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 16:02:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Rain was scattered Wednesday in the South and Northeast, with  
fair conditions in the Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	The moisture stretched from Vermont into New Hampshire, New  
York, Maine and Massachusetts. The Midwest was cloudy and a slight 
rain fell in central Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	In the Southeast, a stationary front produced warm, moist air  
from central Alabama into western Texas. Portions of Texas, the 
Carolinas and southern Virginia received showers and thunderstorms. 
</P>
<P>
	High pressure over the central and northern Plains created clear  
to partly cloudy skies and fair conditions. 
</P>
<P>
	In the West, Montana and Idaho received a few light showers.  
Conditions were fair elsewhere in the region. 
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the Lower 48 states was 89 degrees in Ft.  
Lauderdale, Fla. The low was 28 degrees in Eagle River, Wis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
