<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 17; Nasdaq Is Up 27 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is up 17 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over 
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 27 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up three points. 
</P>
<P>
	With declines in four straight sessions, and seven of the past  
eight, the Dow looks to gain ground today. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's early advance also comes with the Nasdaq composite index  
having hit full correction mode. 
</P>
<P>
	The index, which is often considered a proxy for  
high-technology, has declined ten percent since setting a record 
high one month ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts say Wall Street may finally be seeing some  
bargain-hunting after several sessions of profit-taking. 
</P>
<P>
	Stocks in Europe are mostly higher, after Asian stocks closed  
mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds are narrowly lower. Gold prices have been lower overseas,  
after dropping to 20-year lows yesterday in New York. 
</P>
