<HEADLINE> CNN Titans in Unusual On-Air Tiff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Tensions between CNN President Rick Kaplan and  
``Moneyline'' host Lou Dobbs surfaced in an unusual on-air tiff. 
</P>
<P>
	Dobbs appeared angry last Thursday when he was ordered to cut  
off his financial news program to return to live coverage of 
President Clinton speaking at a news conference in Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	``CNN President Rick Kaplan wants us to return to Littleton,''  
Dobbs said on the air before the shift. 
</P>
<P>
	A day later, a Kaplan deputy issued a memo stating that CNN's  
executive producers have authority to break into the ``Moneyline'' 
broadcast for breaking news or live coverage. A second memo on 
Monday noted that the CNN producer should consult with 
``Moneyline'' executives. 
</P>
<P>
	Dobbs, who is also president of the financial network CNNfn, and  
Kaplan did not want to talk about what happened, spokeswomen said. 
</P>
<P>
	The show runs from 6:30 p.m. to 7:30 p.m. Eastern time on  
weekdays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
