the Los Angeles Dodgers win 9-3 against the Cincinnati Reds. It was 
L.A.'s third victory in 10 games. Unhappy with staff's 4.47 ERA, 
the Dodgers fired pitching coach Charlie Hough and replaced him 
with Triple-A coach Claude Osteen. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by ANDREW DAMPF  
