<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tigers First Baseman on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- The Detroit Tigers placed slumping first baseman  
Tony Clark on the 15-day disabled list today with a ligament sprain 
in his right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	The injury occurred when Clark followed through on a swing  
Tuesday night during the Tigers' 5-3 loss to Toronto. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark was back in the starting lineup Tuesday for the first time  
since being hit in the head by a pitch from Cleveland's Jaret 
Wright on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark, a notoriously slow starter, is off to the worst start of  
his career, batting just .212 with four home runs and 21 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	To replace Clark on the roster, Detroit purchased the contract  
of outfielder Luis Polonia from their Toledo Triple-A club. 
</P>
<P>
	Polonia, 34, is a nine-year veteran who was a non-roster invitee  
to spring training with the Tigers. He was batting .323 with three 
home runs, 22 RBIs and a team-leading 13 stolen bases at Triple-A 
Toledo. 
</P>
<P>
	Polonia batted leadoff and was Detroit's designated hitter  
Wednesday against Toronto. It was his first big-league appearance 
since Sept. 29, 1996 with Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
