<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Seahawks' Coach Seriously Ill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Seattle Seahawks defensive coordinator Fritz  
Shurmur is seriously ill and will take a leave of absence, coach 
Mike Holmgren said today. 
</P>
<P>
	``Fritz has been diagnosed with a serious illness that will  
require a period of extensive treatment,'' Holmgren said in a 
statement. ``It is the hope that the treatment will allow him to 
resume his coaching duties sometime in the future.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Seahawks' public relations office refused to say what was  
wrong with the 66-year-old Shurmur or how long he might be out. 
</P>
<P>
	Shurmur joined the Seahawks during the offseason after serving  
as the Green Bay Packers' defensive coordinator from 1994-98. 
</P>
<P>
	He has coached 24 years in the NFL, including 18 as defensive  
coordinator. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
