<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	 *In the spotlight:* Alanis Morissette was born in Ottawa,  
Canada, on June 1, 1974. She appeared on the sketch-comedy show, 
``You Can't Do That on Television,'' in 1986. As a teen pop singer 
known as Alanis, she released two albums (in Canada only): 
``Alanis'' (1991) and ``Now Is the Time'' (1992). 
</P>
<P>
	 *Breakthrough:* Morissette released her U.S. debut album,  
``Jagged Little Pill,'' in 1995. The collection of tales about 
youthful anxiety and the search for self-esteem struck a nerve 
among pop-rock fans. The CD sold nearly 28 million copies 
worldwide. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1996, she won two Grammys for ``Jagged Little Pill'' and two  
more -- for best rock song and female rock vocal performance -- for 
her lyrically raw single ``You Oughta Know.'' 
</P>
<P>
	As sales soared, Morissette felt the need to withdraw. She even  
traveled to India in search of spiritual renewal. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``Fame was touted as being something that would give me  
the ultimate happiness, and it didn't. So I basically stepped back 
and sat down and stopped for the first time in my life to see who I 
was.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Return:* Her album, ``Supposed Former Infatuation Junkie,'' was  
released in 1998. It debuted at No. 1 on the Billboard charts. But 
after 22 weeks, the album had slipped to No. 100, with fewer than 4 
million copies sold. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this year, the Grammy for best female rock vocal  
performance went to Morissette for ``Uninvited.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Up Next:* Morissette plays the role of God in Kevin Smith's  
film ``Dogma,'' starring Matt Damon, Ben Affleck and Chris Rock. 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for May 30-June 5:  
</P>
<P>
	May 30: Actor Michael J. Pollard is 60. Country singer Wynonna  
is 35. Musician Tom Morello of Rage Against the Machine is 35. 
Musician Patrick Dahlheimer of Live is 28. Rapper Cee-Lo of Goodie 
Mob is 25. 
</P>
<P>
	May 31: Actor-director Clint Eastwood is 69. Actor Tom Berenger  
is 49. Comedian Chris Elliott is 39. Actor Kyle Secor (``Homicide: 
Life on the Street'') is 39. Actress Lea Thompson (``Caroline in 
the City'') is 38. Singer Corey Hart is 37. Rapper Kid Frost is 35. 
Rapper DMC of Run-DMC is 35. Actress Brooke Shields is 34. 
</P>
<P>
	June 1: Actor Andy Griffith is 73. Singer Pat Boone is 65. Actor  
Morgan Freeman is 62. Musician Ron Wood of The Rolling Stones is 
52. Singer Graham Russell of Air Supply is 49. Musician Simon 
Gallup of The Cure is 39. Actor-singer Jason Donovan is 31. Singer 
Alanis Morissette is 25. 
</P>
<P>
	June 2: Actress Sally Kellerman is 62. Actor Stacy Keach is 58.  
Musician Charlie Watts of The Rolling Stones is 58. Actor Jerry 
Mathers (``Leave It to Beaver'') is 51. Actress Joanna Gleason is 
49. Comedian Dana Carvey is 44. Rapper B-Real of Cypress Hill is 
29. Actress Nikki Cox (``Unhappily Ever After'') is 21. Singer 
Irish Grinstead of 702 is 19. 
</P>
<P>
	June 3: Actor Tony Curtis is 74. Singer Curtis Mayfield is 57.  
Singer Suzi Quatro is 49. Musician Billy Powell of Lynyrd Skynyrd 
is 47. Singer Dan Hill is 45. 
</P>
<P>
	June 4: Actor Bruce Dern is 63. Actor Parker Stevenson is 47.  
Singer El DeBarge is 38. Actor Scott Wolf (``Party of Five'') is 
31. Actor Noah Wyle is 28. 
</P>
<P>
	June 5: Actor Spalding Gray is 58. Singer Laurie Anderson is 52.  
Musician Nicko McBrain of Iron Maiden is 45. Musician Kenny G is 
43. Singer Richard Butler of Psychedelic Furs is 43. Singer Brian 
McKnight is 30. Actor Mark Wahlberg is 28. Actor Chad Allen (``Dr. 
Quinn, Medicine Woman'') is 25. Musician P-nut of 311 is 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
