<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-26 21:01:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Burn 2, Fushion 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Jorge Rodriguez scored his first goal of the  
season with five minutes remaining to give the Dallas Burn a 2-1 
Major League Soccer victory Wednesday night over the Miami Fusion. 
</P>
<P>
	The Burn (6-5) moved into second place in the Western  
Conference. Miami (3-8) lost its fifth straight. 
</P>
<P>
	John Jairo Trellez assisted on the winning goal with a pass to  
Mark Santel. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion was playing a man down at the time, as Miami's Jim  
Rooney drew his second yellow card in the 79th minute by pulling 
Trellez down from behind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
