<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Casino Honors Robbie Knievel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Robbie Knievel's jump over a gorge at the Grand  
Canyon last week has landed him a place among some of Las Vegas' 
favorite entertainers and historical figures. 
</P>
<P>
	Knievel -- still on crutches -- was inducted Tuesday into the  
Casino Legends Hall of Fame at the Tropicana Hotel, where other 
members include Frank Sinatra, Howard Hughes and Siegfried and Roy. 
The banged-up bike Knievel used will be put in a glass case. 
</P>
<P>
	Knievel, the son of daredevil Evel Knievel, suffered two cracked  
ribs and a sprained ankle in the 231-foot jump over a 1,500-foot 
Grand Canyon gorge. 
</P>
<P>
	``Everything I do is crazy to the normal person,'' Knievel said.  
``The main reason I do it is to show people how fast a bike can go. 
It is a spiritual, mental and physical feeling before a jump.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Knievel said his next stunt -- a jump over 25 pickup trucks  
parked side by side at the Pikes Peak International Raceway in 
Colorado -- is planned for July 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
