<HEADLINE> Md. Boy Charged in Bra Snapping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALISBURY, Md. (AP) -- A 10-year-old boy has been charged with  
assault for allegedly snapping girls' bras. 
</P>
<P>
	The Pittsville Elementary pupil, who was not identified, was  
accused of assaulting five girls, ages 8 to 11, earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
	He was suspended from school for three days and from a  
county-run, after-school program. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy was charged with four counts of assault for allegedly  
snapping girls' bras and one count of sex offense for allegedly 
touching a girl's buttocks. 
</P>
