Gunnar Solksjaer scored in injury time to give Manchester United 
the Champions League soccer title today with a 2-1 victory over 
Bayern Munich. The goals turned around a game that Bayern had 
controlled since taking the lead in the sixth minute on a free kick 
goal by Mario Basler. 

