<HEADLINE> Cipollini Wins Tour of Italy Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SASSUOLO, Italy (AP) -- Mario Cipollini won a duel of leading  
sprinters Wednesday as he clinched the 12th stage of the Tour of 
Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Riding for the commercial team Saeco, the Italian edged  
compatriot Ivan Quaranta and Dutchman Jeroen Blijlevens at the 
finish line in Sassuolo following a 104.1-mile ride on a mostly 
flat course from Cesenatico. 
</P>
<P>
	French national champion Laurent Jalabert, who finished in a  
large group in the same time as the winner, retained the pink 
jersey of overall leader clinched last Sunday. He held a 
four-second lead over defending Giro champion Marco Pantani. 
</P>
<P>
	Cipollini, upset by younger Quaranta in Tuesday's sprint at  
Cesenatico, scored his 28th career victory in the Italian Tour -- 
his second in three days -- rushing into the lead 200 yards from the 
finish and fighting off Quaranta and Blijlevens. 
</P>
