previous season high for runs in a 17-1 victory over the St. Louis 
Cardinals on Tuesday night. Mark McGwire homered for the fifth time 
in six games, hitting his 13th for St. Louis. The loss was the most 
lopsided for the Cardinals since Atlanta beat them 17-1 on May 8, 
1991. The Cardinals had not allowed so many runs since losing to 
San Diego 17-4 on Aug. 24, 1993. 

